    "body": "The error is thrown in ethers.js [here](https://github.com/ethers-io/ethers.js/blob/ec1b9583039a14a0e0fa15d0a2a6082a2f41cf5b/packages/providers/src.ts/json-rpc-provider.ts#L55-L131) and `checkError` is called [here](https://github.com/ethers-io/ethers.js/blob/ec1b9583039a14a0e0fa15d0a2a6082a2f41cf5b/packages/providers/src.ts/json-rpc-provider.ts#L265) and [here](https://github.com/ethers-io/ethers.js/blob/ec1b9583039a14a0e0fa15d0a2a6082a2f41cf5b/packages/providers/src.ts/json-rpc-provider.ts#L644).\r\n\r\nThe error message is not so user-friendly, but that's what ethors.js and Solidity return. If we modify the error message in Hardhat, users get different error messages depending on where the smart contract code is deployed to (a node on Hardhat or mainnet).\r\n\r\nI think the error message returned by Hardhat to be consistent with what ether.js and Solidity returns. I would submit tickets to ethers.js and Solidity rather than handling in Hardhat.\r\n",
